Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Engineer* role with *Checkr*. I bring over three years of experience building full-stack products and APIs, plus an MS in Computer Science from Pace University, and I am excited by Checkr’s mission to build data products that power safe and fair decisions.

At Sperse, I owned product development from design through release for an MCP interaction layer spanning 1,000+ endpoints, then partnered with product and design stakeholders to ship RESTful API tooling used by Ruby and Javascript teams. I also architected LangChain and LangGraph services with message queues for asynchronous tasks, instrumented Langfuse/LangSmith observability to monitor and resolve production issues, and helped reduce latency by 60% and API cost by 50% while maintaining performant, reliable, scalable, and secure code. At Qualitest, I delivered a LangChain+RAG support chatbot on PostgreSQL that cut ticket resolution time by 20%, and built cloud-agnostic storage APIs across S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO on SQL/NoSQL backends (PostgreSQL and Redis) while leading full-stack IAM development across 30+ applications.

This experience maps directly to the technical depth this position demands: owning features end-to-end, collaborating across engineering, product, and design, and shipping quality software under ambiguity. I also bring the documentation and communication discipline your teams value, including authoring technical guides and leading CUDA/LangChain/LangGraph workshops for 50+ students during my AI Researcher role at Pace.

I am especially motivated by Checkr’s commitment to *fair chance hiring* and to building *trusted workplaces and communities*. Your values of *Ownership* and *Transparency* strongly match how I build and collaborate, and I would value the opportunity to contribute to Checkr’s goal of powering safe and fair decisions through a reliable, customer-centric product platform. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration.

